<br>
What the increase from 16 to 24 bit allows the engine to do is mat textures/geometry more accurately, without &quot;Z-fighting&quot;.  With a 16 bit Z-buffer, items would move from front to back, causing some strange ripple/shimmer effects on some objects, and pronounced jagged edges on others (not to be confused with anti-aliasing).<br>
<br>
